As part of efforts to alleviate poverty as the government eases lockdown over COVID-19 Pandemic, member of the House of
Representatives representing Lagos Mainland Federal Constituency, Hon.
Jide Jimoh has empowered members of his constituency. The empowerment which cuts across members of his constituency
includes youths, artisans and the elderly. The edition which is the 6th edition tagged ‘Economic Assistance
Scheme’ was held at the secretariat of Yaba Local Council Development
Area (LCDA). The lawmaker, who is the Chairman of the House Committee on Regional
Planning and Urban Development, assured his constituency more
dividends of democracy. Jimoh, while reeling out his achievements said, “I have an amazing
relationship with you all and I thank the merciful God for His mercies
upon everyone.” Items distributed included palliatives/cash donations to elderly
(100), cash assistance to youths, deep freezers, grinding machines,
sewing machines, hairdryers, and steamers, auto machine toolbox, auto
spraying machine and facial massagers to mention a few. In his goodwill message, Otunba Tayo Oyemade, an APC chieftain in
Lagos Mainland appreciated Jimoh for reaching out to the people of his
constituency.   